---
import LessonLayout from '../../layouts/LessonLayout.astro';
---
<LessonLayout
  title="Reachy's Feelings"
  track="little-explorers"
  week={8}
  phase="Phase 3: Creative Play"
  duration="30 min"
  emoji="😊"
  objective="Explore how Reachy expresses emotions with its LED eyes"
>
  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-explorer-700 mb-3">🎯 Learning Objective</h2>
    <p class="bg-explorer-50 border-l-4 border-explorer-400 p-4 rounded-r-xl text-gray-700">
      Your child will program Reachy's LED eyes to express different emotions, connecting emotional literacy to robotics.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">🛠️ Materials</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">✅ Computer + Python</li>
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">✅ Emotion face cards (draw happy, sad, surprised, sleepy)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">📋 Activity Steps</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">1</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Feelings Warm-Up (5 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Play "make the face" — parent says an emotion, child makes the face. Now: can a robot make that face? What would it look like?</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">2</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Design Reachy's Emotions (10 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Draw 4 "eye patterns" for: happy, sad, surprised, sleepy. Reachy's eyes are LED displays — they can show any pattern!</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">3</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Emotion Story (10 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Run the code. Tell a 4-scene story: "Reachy woke up HAPPY, then saw something SURPRISING, then felt SLEEPY..." Change the emotions in the code to match!</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">💻 Code Snippet</h2>
    <pre is:raw class="bg-gray-900 text-green-300 rounded-xl p-5 overflow-x-auto text-sm leading-relaxed"><code># feelings.py — Week 8: Little Explorers
import time

EMOTIONS = {
    "happy":     "^‿^ (big bright eyes)",
    "sad":       "◡◡ (droopy eyes)",
    "surprised": "◉◉ (wide open eyes)",
    "sleepy":    "—— (half-closed eyes)",
    "excited":   "★‿★ (star eyes!)",
}

class ReachyMock:
    def show_emotion(self, emotion):
        display = EMOTIONS.get(emotion, "•‿• (neutral)")
        print(f"😊 Reachy's eyes: {display}")
        time.sleep(1.5)

try:
    from reachy_mini import ReachyMini
    robot = ReachyMini()
except Exception:
    robot = ReachyMock()
    print("🎮 Simulator mode")

# Tell a story with emotions!
story = ["happy", "surprised", "excited", "sleepy"]
print("📖 Reachy's Feelings Story:")
for feeling in story:
    robot.show_emotion(feeling)</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">💬 Reflection Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-yellow-800">🌟 "Does Reachy REALLY feel happy? Or is it pretending?"</p></div>
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-yellow-800">🌟 "What emotion did YOU feel today?"</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">👪 Parent Tips</h2>
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-5 text-gray-700">
      <p>💡 The "does Reachy really feel?" question is genuinely philosophical. Honour your child's answer — there's no wrong response, and it sparks great thinking about AI and robots.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</LessonLayout>
